postcontent: Up for sale is my personal Smith and Wesson model 1000 semi-automatic 12 gauge shotgun. This is a one owner gun purchased new in 1976 by me. This shotgun is in AWESOME condition. Very light use on the trap range. Truly a one owner gun for 35 years. I am not a gun dealer so please look closely at the photos and come to your own conclusion regarding condition. The condition was put at 98% by my local gun shop. The Smith & Wesson Model 1000 was produced between 1972 and 1984. It was produced by Howa Machinery in Japan, the same manufacturer of the Howa 1500/Weatherby Vanguard series of rifles. The M1000 is gas operated and is comparable to the Remington 1100. When S&W discontinued the shotgun, the design was taken up by Mossberg. Despite the relatively short production run, the M1000 is built to high standards, and is very reliable. The alloy receiver is engraved and the cap on the pistol grip sports a beautiful Smith and Wesson symbol. This particular gun come with two ribbed barrels. One is 28 inches long and the second is a 30 inches ribbed barrel and both have a modified choke. The finish on the shotgun is in excellent condition. The wood finish is beautiful awesome. With a modified choke, the M1000 would be useful for shooting to medium distances making it useful for hunting or target shooting. The magazine holds 3 rounds plus 1 in the chamber for a total of 4. If you are looking for a dual-purpose shotgun, the M1000 is a fine choice. On the other hand, if you are a collector of all-things Smith and Wesson, the M1000 is a must have. Please take a very good look at the pictures provided and ask any and all questions that you may have before bidding on this item, as I do not offer refunds or exchanges on any of my personal guns items.
